        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): default gateway memory watch off",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Default unset `memorySearch.sync.watch` to `false` for long-lived gateway-mode memory managers.\n- Keep explicit `sync.watch: true` / `false` authoritative, and preserve CLI/status transient defaults.\n- Thread purpose-aware sync resolution through builtin and QMD manager creation, then update config help/docs.\n\nFixes #71335.\n\n## Related Issues And PRs\n\n- #71335 is the exact issue this PR addresses: unset `memorySearch.sync.watch` still resolved to enabled for gateway memory manager paths.\n- #81802 is related FD-pressure work that removed chokidar write-stability polling. It reduced watcher polling FD pressure but intentionally did not change the gateway default policy.\n- #86701 is related FD-pressure work that avoids macOS/Windows per-file watcher fan-out for memory directories. It reduces per-manager watcher cost, but unset gateway managers still allocate watchers unless this default changes.\n- #86293 was a related runtime idle-eviction mitigation for long-running gateway daemons. It bounded manager lifetime, but it was closed and explicitly left the `sync.watch` default out of scope.\n- #64654 was an older extraPaths watcher recursion PR surfaced by search. It is adjacent to memory watcher coverage, not the headless gateway default-policy change.\n- #64549 remains separate: it tracks watch auto-indexing behavior for new files, not the gateway default resource policy.\n- #86613, #77327, and #78224 describe the same FD-pressure family that motivated #81802/#86701; those fixes lower watcher cost but do not make unset gateway watchers conservative.\n- #40389 is related lifecycle cleanup context used by the idle-eviction mitigation, not this default-resolution fix.\n\n## Behavior\n\n- Unset `sync.watch`, no `gateway.mode`: `true` as before.\n- Unset `sync.watch`, `gateway.mode: \"local\"` or `\"remote\"`, default/long-lived manager: `false`.\n- Explicit `sync.watch: true`: `true`, including gateway mode.\n- Explicit `sync.watch: false`: `false`, including gateway mode.\n- CLI/status purposes still resolve unset watch to `true`, and those managers remain transient/no persistent watchers.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/memory-search.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager.watcher-config.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/search-manager.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/memory-search.ts src/agents/memory-search.test.ts src/config/types.tools.ts src/config/schema.help.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/search-manager.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager.watcher-config.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts docs/concepts/memory-builtin.md docs/reference/memory-config.md`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD`\n",
        "branch": "codex/fd-gateway-memory-watch-default",
